%N A378965 Semiperimeter of the unique primitive Pythagorean triple (x,y,z) such that (x-y+z)/2 is A002315(n) and such that its long leg and its hypotenuse are consecutive natural numbers.
%D A378965 Miguel Ángel Pérez García-Ortega, José Manuel Sánchez Muñoz and José Miguel Blanco Casado, El Libro de las Ternas Pitagóricas, Preprint 2024.
%H A378965 Andrew Howroyd, <a href="/A378965/b378965.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..200</a>
%H A378965 <a href="/index/Rec#order_05">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (41,-246,246,-41,1).
%F A378965 a(n) = (A362545(n) + 2*A377726(n) + 1)/2.
%F A378965 a(n) = A002315(n)*(2*A002315(n) - 1).
%F A378965 G.f.: (1 + 50*x - 164*x^2 - 18*x^3 + 3*x^4)/((1 - x)*(1 - 34*x + x^2)*(1 - 6*x + x^2)). - _Andrew Howroyd_, Nov 17 2025
%e A378965 For n=1, the short leg is A362545(1) = 13, the long leg is A377726(1) = 84 and the hypotenuse is A377726(1) + 1 = 85 so the semiperimeter is then a(1) = (13 + 84 + 85)/2 = 91.
%t A378965 s[n_]:=s[n]=Module[{ra},ra=((1+Sqrt[2])^(2n+1)-(Sqrt[2]-1)^(2n+1))/2;{ra(2ra-1)}];semis={};Do[semis=Join[semis,FullSimplify[s[n]]],{n,0,17}];semis
